ğŸ”¸ Time & Space
Time: O(nÂ³)
Space: O(set size)
âŒ Too slow for large input

//Better -- using formula
We try to find the third number
int num = -(nums[i]+nums[j]);
ğŸ”¹ Explanation We want:
nums[i] + nums[j] + num = 0
So,
num = -(nums[i] + nums[j])
This is the required third number.

public List<List<Integer>> threeSum(int[] nums) {
        HashSet<List<Integer>> result = new HashSet<>();
        int n = nums.length;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            HashSet<Integer> sset = new HashSet<>();
            for(int j=i+1;j<n;j++){
                int num = -(nums[i]+nums[j]);
                if(sset.contains(num)){
                    List<Integer> arr = Arrays.asList(nums[i], nums[j], num);
                    Collections.sort(arr);
                    result.add(arr);
                }

                sset.add(nums[j]);
            }
        }
        return new ArrayList<>(result);
    }
â±ï¸ Complexity
Time: O(nÂ²)
Space: O(n) (HashSet)

//Optimal
    public List<List<Integer>> threeSum(int[] nums) {
        List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int n = nums.length;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(i>0 && nums[i] == nums[i-1]) continue;
            int j = i+1;
            int k = n-1;

            while(j<k){
                int sum = nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k];
                if(sum == 0){
                    result.add(Arrays.asList(nums[i], nums[j], nums[k]));
                    j++;
                    k--;
                    while(j<k && nums[j] == nums[j-1]) j++;
                    while(j<k && nums[k] == nums[k+1]) k--;
                }
                else if(sum > 0){
                    k--;
                }
                else{
                    j++;
                }
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}
